computation<NOTE N="x" PLACE="foot">See John Walker's attempt towards recovering an account of the num|bers and &s;ufferings of the clergy. The parliament pretended to leave the &s;eque&s;|$$red clergy a fifth of their revenue; but this author makes it &s;ufficiently appear, that this provi&s;ion, &s;mall as it is, was never regularly paid the ejected clergy.</NOTE>, it appears, that above one half of
the e&s;tabli&s;hed clergy had been turned out to beggary
