who&s;e countenance they had at fir&s;t embraced that pro|fe&s;&s;ion.
To renounce epi&s;copacy and the liturgy, and
to &s;ub&s;cribe the covenant, were the only terms, which
could &s;ave them from &s;o rigorous a fate; and if the lea&s;t
mark of malignancy, as it was called, or affection to
<PB N="94" REF="138">
<GAP DESC="DUPLICATE" EXTENT="1 page">
