<GAP DESC="DUPLICATE" EXTENT="1 page">
<PB N="96" REF="140">
the King, who &s;o intirely loved them, had ever e&s;cape
their lips, even this hard choice was not permitted. Th$
&s;acred character, which gives the prie&s;thood &s;uch autho$rity
over mankind, becoming more venerable from th$
&s;ufferings, endured for the &s;ake of principle, by the$
